Warren Hilton Shanabrook (November 30, 1880 â€“ March 10, 1964) was a Major League Baseball third baseman.  Shanabrook played for the Washington Senators in .  In one career game, he had no hits in two at-bats. He batted and threw right-handed.
Shanabrook was born in Massillon, Ohio and died in North Canton, Ohio.
